<!-- Stamp -->
<section id="stamp">
  <h2>data-stamp</h2>
  <p>Rubber stamp effect with a fractal noise SVG filter, rotation, and <code>mix-blend-mode: multiply</code>. Renders uppercase, bold text inside a thick border with a worn, inked texture. Requires JS to inject the SVG noise filter.</p>

  <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Stamp colors">{{ stampCode | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>Rotation Modifiers</h3>
  <p>Control the tilt angle with space-separated modifiers:</p>
  <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Stamp rotation">{{ stampModCode | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>Attributes</h3>
  <table class="props-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Values</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>data-stamp</code></td><td><code>""</code>, <code>"red"</code>, <code>"blue"</code>, <code>"green"</code>, <code>"black"</code>, <code>"gold"</code></td><td>Stamp ink color preset. Empty defaults to red.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>(modifier) <code>straight</code></td><td>space-separated</td><td>Remove rotation (0deg).</td></tr>
      <tr><td>(modifier) <code>slight</code></td><td>space-separated</td><td>Reduce rotation to -2deg.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>(modifier) <code>heavy</code></td><td>space-separated</td><td>Increase rotation to -8deg.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>CSS Custom Properties</h3>
  <table class="props-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Property</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>--vb-stamp-color</code></td><td>Per preset</td><td>Ink color in OKLCH.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<!-- Marquee -->
<section id="marquee">
  <h2>data-marquee</h2>
  <p>Continuously scrolling horizontal content with edge masking. Children animate left (or right with <code>reverse</code>) in an infinite loop. Reduced-motion fallback enables horizontal scrolling instead.</p>

  <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic marquee">{{ marqueeCode | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>Variants</h3>
  <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Marquee variants">{{ marqueeVarCode | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>Hover Pause</h3>
  <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Hover to pause">{{ marqueeHoverCode | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>Attributes</h3>
  <table class="props-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Values</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>data-marquee</code></td><td><code>""</code>, <code>"reverse"</code>, <code>"slow"</code> (40s), <code>"fast"</code> (8s), <code>"pause"</code></td><td>Direction, speed, or paused state.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>(modifier) <code>hover-pause</code></td><td>space-separated</td><td>Pause animation on hover.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>CSS Custom Properties</h3>
  <table class="props-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Property</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>--vb-marquee-speed</code></td><td><code>20s</code></td><td>Scroll animation duration.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>--vb-marquee-gap</code></td><td><code>var(--size-xl, 3rem)</code></td><td>Gap between repeating items.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<!-- Flipboard -->
<section id="flipboard">
  <h2>data-flipboard</h2>
  <p>Split-flap departure board effect. Each character sits in a dark cell with a horizontal hinge and cycles through random letters before settling on the target character. Requires JS initialization.</p>

  <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Flipboard">{{ flipboardCode | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>Attributes</h3>
  <table class="props-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Values</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>data-flipboard</code></td><td>boolean</td><td>Enables the split-flap effect on the element's text content.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>CSS Custom Properties</h3>
  <table class="props-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Property</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>--vb-flip-ms</code></td><td><code>60ms</code></td><td>Duration of each character flip animation.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Timing</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Each character flips 4&ndash;10 times randomly before settling</li>
    <li>Dwell between flips: 30ms</li>
    <li>Character stagger: 80ms (left-to-right reveal)</li>
    <li>Flippable characters: <code>A&ndash;Z 0&ndash;9 . , : ! ? / -</code> and space</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>JavaScript API</h3>
  <p>The <code>data-flipboard</code> JS init registers via the retro pack. The following functions are available on initialized elements:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>replayFlipboard(el)</code> &mdash; restart the flip animation</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<!-- Shared Behavior -->
<section>
  <h2>Shared Behavior</h2>

  <h3>Progressive Enhancement</h3>
  <p><code>data-stamp</code> and <code>data-marquee</code> are CSS-only (stamp needs a small JS filter injection). <code>data-flipboard</code> requires JS &mdash; without it, the text displays normally.</p>

  <h3>Reduced Motion</h3>
  <p>All animations respect <code>prefers-reduced-motion: reduce</code> and <code>:root[data-motion-reduced]</code>. Marquee falls back to horizontal scroll; flipboard displays characters immediately without flipping.</p>

  <h3>Print</h3>
  <p>Animations and filters are stripped in print media.</p>

  <h3>CSS Layer</h3>
  <p>All rules are scoped to <code>@layer bundle-effects</code>.</p>
</section>

